administrators who built it,

01:21:54.217 --> 01:21:57.729
indeed the endowment of the
corpus of scholarly work

01:21:57.729 --> 01:22:00.481
that comes from generations
and generations before us

01:22:00.481 --> 01:22:02.640
and you know this very well.

01:22:02.640 --> 01:22:06.484
And so I have a feeling
that that endowment

01:22:06.484 --> 01:22:09.415
gets built up over time,
sometimes it also involves

01:22:09.415 --> 01:22:11.474
an endowment of money and you're right

01:22:11.474 --> 01:22:15.650
it involves an endowment of
purposes that's for sure.

01:22:15.650 --> 01:22:18.150
And I don't want to fight you,

01:22:19.946 --> 01:22:22.755
especially you to the death about

01:22:22.755 --> 01:22:25.408
rejecting the concept of legitimacy.

01:22:25.408 --> 01:22:28.915
But there my sense is, wow we would could

01:22:28.915 --> 01:22:32.798
dissipate this thing pretty
quickly, for example,

01:22:32.798 --> 01:22:36.671
if just let me do a really
worst case scenario.

01:22:36.671 --> 01:22:38.104
Berkeley desperately needs money.

01:22:38.104 --> 01:22:39.533
It decides a Berkeley degree

01:22:39.533 --> 01:22:42.006
because of the brand
is really worth a lot,

01:22:42.006 --> 01:22:44.497
and so it will just sell them.

01:22:44.497 --> 01:22:46.783
Something very similar by the way happened

01:22:46.783 --> 01:22:48.712
before the French Revolution
when the French state

01:22:48.712 --> 01:22:51.926
was desperate to raise
money and it sold offices.

01:22:51.926 --> 01:22:54.254
And actually the English Crown did it

01:22:54.254 --> 01:22:55.596
before the English Revolution also.

01:22:55.596 --> 01:22:57.669
They sold baronets.

01:22:57.669 --> 01:23:00.908
You know it's not impossible
if you're desperate enough

01:23:00.908 --> 01:23:03.287
and you just would sell
degrees or sell them

01:23:03.287 --> 01:23:06.787
for some minimal amount of symbolic effort

01:23:08.031 --> 01:23:10.339
knowing full well they didn't
really represent anything

01:23:10.339 --> 01:23:13.375
and then you would
spend up that endowment,

01:23:13.375 --> 01:23:15.981
you would deplete it almost overnight.

01:23:15.981 --> 01:23:20.122
So that's the sense in
which I think of endowment

01:23:20.122 --> 01:23:24.289
as that sort of accumulated set
of commitments and resources

01:23:27.453 --> 01:23:30.453
and so I guess that's how I mean it.

01:23:31.369 --> 01:23:33.120
Now, I agree with you.

01:23:33.120 --> 01:23:34.915
The reason I don't like
the term legitimacy

01:23:34.915 --> 01:23:37.555
